ROGUELIKE DUNGEON EXPLORER - JAVA SETUP GUIDE
=============================================

1. CREATE A NEW PROJECT IN ECLIPSE:
   - Open Eclipse
   - File > New > Java Project
   - Project name: "RoguelikeDungeon"
   - Click Finish

2. COPY SOURCE FILES:
   - Copy all .java files to: src/
   - The project should have all these files:
     * RoguelikeGame.java (main entry point)
     * GamePanel.java (game loop)
     * InputHandler.java (keyboard input)
     * Dungeon.java (level generation)
     * Player.java (player stats)
     * Enemy.java (enemy AI)
     * Trap.java (trap system)
     * Loot.java (loot items)
     * Item.java (item definitions)
     * Inventory.java (inventory management)
     * LootGenerator.java (random loot)
     * DungeonTheme.java (dungeon themes)
     * GameRenderer.java (graphics rendering)
     * GameState.java (game states)

3. RUN THE GAME:
   - Right-click on RoguelikeGame.java
   - Run As > Java Application
   - The game window will open automatically

GAME CONTROLS:
==============
- Arrow Keys or WASD: Move around
- Space: Attack adjacent enemies
- Q: Quit game
- R: Restart after game over

GAME FEATURES:
==============
✓ Procedurally generated dungeons
✓ 5 enemy types with scaling difficulty
✓ 4 dungeon themes (Stone, Ice, Obsidian, Corrupted)
✓ Multiple dungeon levels with progression
✓ Trap system (4 different trap types)
✓ Item and loot system
✓ Inventory management
✓ Combat system with hit chances
✓ Enemy AI with pathfinding
✓ Health/mana bars
✓ Experience and leveling system
✓ Permadeath roguelike mechanics
✓ Glowing torch effects and atmospheric lighting

GAMEPLAY GUIDE:
===============
1. Explore the dungeon and defeat enemies
2. Collect loot to improve your stats
3. Find the stairs (golden square with glow) to go to the next level
4. Each level gets harder with more enemies and better loot
5. If you die, restart with R or quit with Q
6. Get stronger, explore deeper, and survive as long as possible!

ENEMY TYPES:
============
- Goblin: Weak, common (green)
- Skeleton: Medium, decaying (white)
- Orc: Strong, armored (brown)
- Troll: Very strong, regenerating (purple)
- Demon: Boss-level, powerful (red)

DUNGEON THEMES:
===============
- Level 1: Stone Dungeon (gray/orange torches)
- Level 2: Ice Cavern (blue/cyan torches)
- Level 3: Obsidian Fortress (dark gray/red torches)
- Level 4+: Corrupted Temple (purple/pink torches)
(Themes repeat with escalating difficulty)

CUSTOMIZATION:
==============
You can modify these values in the source code:
- GamePanel.java: WIDTH, HEIGHT, TILE_SIZE
- Dungeon.java: Enemy spawn count and type
- Player.java: Starting stats (health, mana, attack, defense)
- DungeonTheme.java: Color schemes
- Enemy.java: Enemy stats scaling

NO EXTERNAL DEPENDENCIES REQUIRED!
All code uses standard Java Swing libraries.

If you have any issues, ensure:
1. Java 8+ is installed
2. Eclipse is up to date
3. All .java files are in the src/ folder
4. No syntax errors shown in Eclipse
